Yang-Mills Lagrangian to the effective action, but the gauge
coupling will be a function of the scalar fields. If we redefine
the gauge field to absorb these factors so that the gauge
coupling is constant, we are effectively introducing charges to
the scalar fields. We will not pursue this effect here.





