Exact solutions 


In the above we studied numerically models of two scalar fields
with the exponential potential V =
e^b_1 +e^c_1+d_2 . In fact, exact solutions can
also be obtained. From the ansatz  _i = p_i
t + q_i, H = h t , we find the solution &p_1=-2 b , p_2=-2(b-c) bd , 

&e^bq_1 =2(3h-1)(d^2-c(b-c)) b^2 d^2 , e^cq_1+dq_2 =2(3h-1)(b-c) bd^2 , and h =
2(d^2+(b-c)^2) b^2 d^2 . These special solutions are either acceleration for all  or
deceleration for all . The condition for acceleration is .
For the potentials from compactification on  in
Sec , h=m_1+m_2 m_1+m_2+2  < 1, and there is
no inflation. For the hypothetical model () we studied
numerically in the previous subsection, .

To understand the form and simplicity of these solutions it is
useful to change variables from  to . For the case
where the extra dimensions are , we have b=2, c=1, d=3 , 

p_1=-1, p_2=-1 3  . 


The time dependence of the 's is given by
 

